          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "28f1c378d01673d4b58ae0b8c7d35631",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Beast",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 453,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "A creature similar to an animal but with an Intelligence modifier of \u20133 or higher is usually a beast. Unlike an animal, a beast might be able to speak and reason.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "9a500f60cf6f1b2c699642751076425e",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Centaur",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "1.1",
                "aonid": 221,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "1.1",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Monster Core pg. 362",
                "aonid": 221,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Monster Core pg. 362",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Monster Core",
              "page": 362,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Centaurs have humanoid upper bodies and equine lower bodies.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 91,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "creature_type"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "0c7ddd2d1aff745e1b670b9eb846114e",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Humanoid",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 457",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 457",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 457,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Humanoid creatures reason and act much like humans. They typically stand upright and have two arms and two legs.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "40b5d9c5e49dbe2aea5d7ecf38d950f3",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Mythic",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "War of Immortals pg. 69",
                "aonid": 232,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "War of Immortals pg. 69",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "War of Immortals",
              "page": 69,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Options with this trait grant or utilize mythic power. Feats with the mythic trait can only be taken by mythic characters, who are typically characters with a mythic Calling.  \n  \n Monsters with the mythic trait have access to a pool of Mythic Points and are particularly strong for creatures of their level. Many mythic monsters are either resistant or entirely immune to attacks from non-mythic creatures and weapons.  \n  \n Spells with the mythic trait require the expenditure of a Mythic Point in order to be cast, and items with the mythic trait require the expenditure of a Mythic Point in order to use their activated abilities.  \n  \n Weapons with the mythic trait overcome the resistances and immunities of mythic monsters.",
          "type": "trait"
        }
      ],
      "type": "stat_block_section"
